The paper deals with the computation of persistent homology groups over directed acyclic graphs (DAGs), which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the application of these tools to point-cloud data, which is a topic in computational topology (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper presents an algorithm for computing persistent homology groups, which is a topic in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these tools for detecting significant barcodes, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
